      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "No worries, I got a bit carried away with the goblin analogies. Let's focus on the car issue. The squealing noise from the front passenger side when braking is likely due to worn-out brake pads or warped rotors. In this case, it's a relatively common problem that can be fixed by a mechanic.\n\nIf you're comfortable with DIY repairs, you can try replacing the brake pads yourself. However, if you're not familiar with brake work or if the issue is more complex, it's recommended to have a professional mechanic take a look. They can assess the situation and provide a more accurate diagnosis.\n\nIt's also worth noting that if the rotors are warped, they may need to be resurfaced or replaced, which can be a more involved process. In this case, it's best to have a mechanic handle it to ensure the job is done correctly and safely.\n\nIf you're not sure what to do, you can try to bleed the brake system to see if that resolves the issue. But if the problem persists, it's best to have a mechanic take a closer look.",
